{{Source Citation|date=June 2023}} [[File:Hitsujisaki jinja Sourintou.JPG|thumb|{{ill|Reiyousaki Shrine (Ishinomaki City Minato)|nl|Reiyousaki Shrine (Ishinomaki City Minato)|ja|零羊崎神社 (石巻市湊)|zh|零羊崎神社 (石巻市湊)|lt=Reiyousaki Shrine|lt_ja=零羊崎神社|lt_nl=Reiyousaki Shrine|lt_zh=零羊崎神社|12=draft}} Sōrintō]]
'''Sorintou''' (相輪橖) is one of the {{ill|Buddhism|nl|boeddhisme|ja|仏教|zh|佛教|12=draft}} facilities. It is also written as '''Sorintou'''.
==Overview== It has a shape resembling a rocket, and its height is {{Nowrap|13.7 {{ill|Meter|nl|meter|ja|メートル|zh|米|lt=m|lt_ja=m|lt_nl=m|lt_zh=m|12=draft}}}}. It is considered a type of {{ill|Buddhist Pagoda|nl|Buddhist Pagoda|ja|仏塔|zh|佛塔|12=draft}}, and by removing the roof sections of {{ill|Three-storied pagoda|ja|三重塔|zh|三重塔|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Five-storied pagoda|8=ja|9=五重塔|12=draft|lt=Five-storied pagoda|12=draft}}, it is composed of pillars and the {{ill|ring of eaves|nl|ring of eaves|ja|相輪|zh|相轮|12=draft}} located on top of the pagoda roof, with supporting pillars extending in four directions. Although they appear to have been constructed long ago, few historical Sorintou remain today, with examples found at {{ill|Enryaku-ji Temple|nl|Enryaku-ji Temple|ja|比叡山延暦寺|zh|比叡山延暦寺|12=draft}}, {{ill|Rinno-ji Temple|nl|Rinno-ji Temple|ja|輪王寺|zh|輪王寺|lt=Nikkoyama Rinno-ji|lt_ja=日光山輪王寺|lt_nl=Nikkoyama Rinno-ji|lt_zh=日光山輪王寺|12=draft}}, and at Nishiren-ji in Namegata City.
<gallery> Sorinto.jpg|Enryaku-ji West Tower Sorinto of Rinno Temple.jpg|Rinno-ji Temple Sorinto of Sairen-ji Temple in Namegata city,IBARAKI,Japan.jpg|Ibaraki · {{ill|Nishiren-ji Temple (Namegata)|nl|Nishiren-ji Temple (Namegata)|ja|西蓮寺 (行方市)|zh|西莲寺 (行方市)|lt=Nishiren-ji|lt_ja=西蓮寺|lt_nl=Nishiren-ji|lt_zh=西莲寺|12=draft}} Tairyu-ji, Sōrin Tower 01.jpg|{{ill|Tokushima Prefecture|nl|Tokushima Prefecture|ja|徳島県|zh|德岛县|12=draft}} {{ill|Tairyu-ji Temple|nl|Tairyu-ji Temple|ja|太龍寺|zh|太龍寺|12=draft}} </gallery>
